Quora programming challenge 1: Duct-cooling
Frederic Spieler, Feb 27 2012
E-mail : fred@fredspieler.com
Web    : hire.fredspieler.com

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Files included in spieler_duct.tar:
-README (this file)
-input (the test input provided by Quora)
-source.c (the sole C source file)
-makefile (VERY simple makefile)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Linux instructions:

How to compile:
make

How to run:
cat <input file> | ./duct

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Other instructions:

There are primary two possible changes one could make to the C source
file: enabling the timer and enabling the continuity assumption (see
source file for more explanation).

The timer can be enabled by changing line 18 to
#define TIMER ON

The continuity optimization can be enabled by changing line 19 to
#define CONT_OPT ON

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Results:

size 7x8 (test input given by Quora, in file named "input")
Solution     : 301716 paths

On Core2 T5300 @ 1.73 GHz, running Ubuntu 11.10, single trial time:
CONT_OPT on  : 1.630666 s
CONT_OPT off : 2.066694 s
